cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.LG, cs.CR

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a new routing protocol for Wireless Body Area Sensor Networks (WBASNs) which involves communication and networking.
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper presents a Linear Programming (LP) model for maximum information extraction and minimum energy consumption.
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper introduces mobility support and energy-management to overcome the disconnection problem caused by continuous mobility of human body.
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possible category as the paper may involve the use of machine learning techniques for thermal-aware routing.
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is also a possible category as the paper may discuss security issues related to WBASNs.
